<item>
  <title>Linux Permissions</title>
  <dc:creator>Caleb Grant</dc:creator>
  <link>http://toolkit.goecoug.com/blog/posts/linux-permissions/index.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<section id="syntax" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="syntax">Syntax</h2>
<p>General: <code>_rwxrwxrwx 1 owner group</code></p>
<p><code>_ | rwx | rwx | rwx</code> = Special | Owner | Group | All Users</p>
<section id="shorthand" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="shorthand">Shorthand</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>4</code> | <code>r</code> = Read</li>
<li><code>2</code> | <code>w</code> = Write</li>
<li><code>1</code> | <code>x</code> = Execute</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="detailed" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="detailed">Detailed</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>0</code> = <code>---</code></li>
<li><code>1</code> = <code>--x</code></li>
<li><code>2</code> = <code>-w-</code></li>
<li><code>3</code> = <code>-wx</code></li>
<li><code>4</code> = <code>r-</code></li>
<li><code>5</code> = <code>r-x</code></li>
<li><code>6</code> = <code>rw-</code></li>
<li><code>7</code> = <code>rwx</code></li>
</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section id="commands" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="commands">Commands</h2>
<p><code>chgrp</code> = Change group</p>
<p><em>Example</em>: <code>sudo chgrp -R &lt;group&gt; &lt;folder&gt;</code></p>
<p><code>chown</code> = Change ownership</p>
<p><em>Example</em>: <code>sudo chown -R &lt;user&gt;:&lt;group&gt; &lt;file/folder&gt;</code></p>
<p><code>chmod</code> = Change permissions</p>
<p><em>Example</em>: <code>sudo chmod -R 774 &lt;file/folder&gt;</code></p>
<p>Make new files inherit the group: <code>sudo chmod g+s &lt;folder&gt;</code></p>
<section id="example" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="example">Example</h3>
<p>Create a shared directory for a group.1. Create a shared directory for users to access: <code>/share</code></p>
<ol type="1">
<li>Assign users to a common group (staff): <code>sudo usermod -a -G staff &lt;user&gt;</code></li>
<li>Verify user groups: <code>groups &lt;user&gt;</code></li>
<li>Create shared directory and assign permissions:</li>
</ol>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb1-1"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">sudo</span> mkdir /share <span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="dt" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">\</span></span>
<span id="cb1-2"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">sudo</span> chgrp <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-R</span> staff /share <span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="ex" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">\ #</span> assign group</span>
<span id="cb1-3"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">sudo</span> chmod <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-R</span> g+w /share <span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="ex" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">\ #</span> permissions</span>
<span id="cb1-4"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">sudo</span> chmod <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-R</span> +s /share <span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;"># inherit permissions for newly created files/folders</span></span></code></pre></div>


</section>
</section>

 ]]></description>
